{"questionId":"11762","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Beth goes for a run. She uses a fitness app to record her distance, <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"s\">\n  <mi>s</mi>\n</math></span> km, and time, <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"t\">\n  <mi>t</mi>\n</math></span> minutes. A graph of her distance against time is shown.</p>\n<p><img src=\"__IMG__/9b0dc42c50234d45f5e8eeb2bca3c40136e3ff8f.png\"></p>\n<p>Beth runs at a constant speed of 2.3 ms<sup>–1</sup>&nbsp;for the first 8 minutes.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Calculate her distance after 8 minutes. Give your answer in km, correct to 3 decimal places.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{{2.3 \\times 8 \\times 60}}{{1000}} = 1.104\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>2.3</mn>\n      <mo>×</mo>\n      <mn>8</mn>\n      <mo>×</mo>\n      <mn>60</mn>\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>1000</mn>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>1.104</mn>\n</math></span>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>M1A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"11762","referenceCode":"EXM.2.AHL.TZ0.13a","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Calculate her distance after 8 minutes. Give your answer in km, correct to 3 decimal places.","paper":"2","level":"HL","questionNumber":"a","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 2—Functions","Topic 2—Functions","AHL 2.9—HL modelling functions"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}